\title{Definition of Logical Connectives}
\date{2024-02-09}
\author{mbryant}
\taxon{definition}

\p{We use logical connectives to assess truth value of a formula in propositional and first order logic.}
\p{The symbol #{\lor} corresponds to the English word "or". We say #{A \lor B} is true if #{A} or #{B} is true under their respective truth assignments****.}
\p{The symbol #{\land} corresponds to the English word "and". We say #{A\land B} is true if #{A} and #{B} are both true under their respective truth assignments.}
\p{The symbol #{\neg} corresponds to the English word "not". We say #{\neg A} is true if #{A} is false.}
